name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: The state of our state is strong. It is forward-thinking. It is dynamic. It is bold. And it is courageous.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Colorado has always been a state of trailblazers. Ours is a state of can-do people. We don‚Äôt back down from a challenge, and we don‚Äôt quit when the going gets tough.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Here's what the renewable energy future looks like: innovating, growing jobs, growing opportunity, saving people money, and doing our part to reduce the harmful effects of climate change and local air pollution in the process.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: The states and countries that embrace the renewable energy future will reap the economic rewards. That‚Äôs why we have taken bold action to put us on the path to achieving 100% renewable energy by 2040.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We are never going to solve climate change or air quality issues if everyone looks at the person next to them and says 'YOU do something about the climate.‚Äô

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We‚Äôre spending more and more time sitting in traffic, which means less and less time with our loved ones. Thanks to good-faith bipartisan legislative work, the state was able to make a historic multi-year investment in transportation infrastructure.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We are asking the Legislature for a one-time infusion from the General Fund to make important capacity improvements across our state parks system. This money will also go towards opening our newest state park ‚Äî Fishers Peak!

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Our majestic lands define our state and power our economy by making us an international destination for tourism and outdoor recreation.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: I‚Äôm hopeful we can construct a unique Colorado solution that provides paid time off to many more Coloradans as soon as possible, without straining state resources or forcing taxpayers to bear the financial risk.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We need to find a way to enact paid family and medical leave for more Coloradans. The Federal Family and Medical Leave Act allows for unpaid leave, but that still forces families to choose between getting a paycheck and caring for a newborn child, an aging parent, or themselves.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Reducing costs in our health care system will also help us tackle one of our most pressing problems ‚Äî our state‚Äôs mental health and addiction crisis.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Special interests are going to fight legislation that will bring some sanity to the pricing. But we don‚Äôt represent the special interests -- we represent the people. And the people are crying out for relief from high health care costs.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We know that health care costs won‚Äôt magically go down on their own. We need to keep working. This year I‚Äôm supporting legislation to require prescription drug price transparency & provide Coloradans a public option to increase freedom & choice in the health care marketplace.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Thanks to reinsurance, health care rates on the individual market are going down by an average of 20%! And the savings are greatest in the Eastern Plains, Southern Colorado, and the Western Slope!

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Perhaps the biggest accomplishment in health care last year was our reinsurance program -- a bipartisan effort led by Representatives @McCluskieforCO and Janice Rich and Senators @KerryDonovanSD5 and Bob Rankin.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: The cost of health care is starting to change for the better, thanks to bipartisan work -- and the work of our tremendous @LTGovofCO Dianne Primavera who is heading up our Office of Saving People Money on Health Care.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: There is one issue that continues to reign over all when it comes to affordability: the high cost of health care. 13% of Americans -- 1 out of every 8 people who live in this country -- said they knew someone who died because they could not afford treatment. This. Must. Change.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: As we work to broaden our tax base and lower the rate, we must start today on saving more for a rainy day. We have an obligation to save during prosperous times like these so we can weather the next storm whenever it comes.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We also delivered a tax cut for 144,000 small businesses in Colorado by cutting wasteful subsidies to big-box retailers, and we still had money left over to invest in affordable housing and improving health care.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: This year, due to our strong economy and a bipartisan deal from 2005, every Coloradan will receive real tax relief as our Colorado income taxes go down to a historic low of 4.5%. This tax cut applies to all taxpayers, including individuals, corporations, and every small business.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We don‚Äôt build walls of exclusion in Colorado ‚Äî we build ladders of opportunity!

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: In the face of unprecedented hostility from this White House toward our immigrant communities, we say loudly and proudly that we stand with DREAMers and refugees!

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Here we believe your future should not be pre-determined by the color of your skin, your parents‚Äô income, your religion, your age, your disability status, where you live in our great state, where you were born, who you love, your gender identity. We believe in a Colorado For All.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We need to keep our economy strong, but more importantly ‚Äî we need to make sure our economy works for everyone.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: I also want to highlight the next important affordability effort: The ‚ÄúGet On Your Feet‚Äù loan forgiveness plan. It would provide debt relief to Coloradans who graduate from 2- or 4-year colleges on an income-based repayment program, helping them transition into the workforce.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Thanks to new legislation enacted last year, we are putting $100 into a college savings account for every single Colorado child born or adopted beginning January 1st of this year.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Every child deserves a safe opportunity to learn, make friends, create memories, grow up, graduate, and move on to a successful life.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: One of the most difficult days of my administration was responding to the STEM school shooting in Highlands Ranch. 8 students were injured, and Kendrick Castillo lost his life heroically preventing more bloodshed. Kendrick‚Äôs parents, John and Maria, are here with us today

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Our work on education is incredibly important. But we can‚Äôt fulfill our promise of a better future for our kids if we don‚Äôt do a better job of keeping them safe when they walk through the schoolhouse door.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Because of our fiscal rules, the state spends far too much backfilling some of the wealthiest school districts in the state. That is truly at the root of our school funding issues. Together, we can fix this systemic problem and finally raise pay for our hardworking educators.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Our teachers, making up one of the most important professions in our society, shouldn‚Äôt have to work a 2nd or 3rd job just to make ends meet.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: We can and we must do better, which is why I‚Äôm committed to achieving universal access to quality preschool for 4-year-olds by the end of my first term.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Now it‚Äôs time to take the next step: In my budget this year, we‚Äôre proposing to fund preschool for an additional 6,000 children, which for the first time will bring coverage to half of all eligible kids in Colorado.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Because of free full-day kindergarten, Samantha Hosmer, a mother of two from Erie, Colorado, is saving over $300 dollars a month, and Samantha was able to return to full-time work as a special ed paraprofessional.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: That pathway to prosperity often starts with a great education.  Last year at this podium, I asked legislators to take the bold step of providing free full-day kindergarten for every kid in Colorado. And we delivered!

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: It's our job to build a state that will allow Coloradans to reach the mountaintop - by saving families money, protecting the natural wonders that grace every corner of our state, & widening the pathway to prosperity, instead of leaving folks feeling like they‚Äôre running in place.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: 95% of the bills that I signed into law last year were passed with Republican and Democratic votes! We should not take this cooperative spirit for granted. Because the notion that we‚Äôre all in this together is a much better approach to solving problems than trying to go it alone.

name: Governor Jared Polis
tweet: Working together last year, we lowered health care costs, lowered taxes for small businesses, provided more affordable housing, made the largest-ever state investment in transportation, and delivered universal free Full Day Kindergarten for all! #copolitics #coleg
